snippet.title: Analyzing the Extreme Differences Between Meghan & Harry and William & Kate in Engagement Interviews
snippet.description:
This is a linguistic comparison of Prince Harry/Meghan Markle’s engagement interview and Prince William/Kate Middleton’s engagement interview. What are some of the most telling differences between the couples’ statements, and what do the statements say about their relationships? 

*Like, Comment, Subscribe*

This video has an educational purpose and is made according to the terms of ‘fair use’.

Statement Analysis (SA): focuses on unreliable language. SA is the objective and detailed analysis of a subject’s language. The purpose of SA is to present an argument to be used in an investigation. The method is used in FBI training.

Conversation Analysis (CA): a method used in academia and with a primary focus on daily conversations. CA concentrates on pauses, interruptions, turn-taking, and other phenomena that influence a conversation.
